Now, you might be surprised to hear

00:13:04.491 --> 00:13:05.881
that we aren’t going to talk about

00:13:05.881 --> 00:13:07.721
Liz Truss at all in this episode.

00:13:08.261 --> 00:13:09.691
And that’s for two reasons.

00:13:10.221 --> 00:13:12.931
Firstly, it’s not completely unusual,

00:13:13.281 --> 00:13:15.511
and although there are plenty of unusual

00:13:15.511 --> 00:13:17.851
and unexpected bits of her chaotic

00:13:17.861 --> 00:13:19.491
44 days in charge of the country,

00:13:19.841 --> 00:13:22.011
you probably know some of it already.

00:13:22.871 --> 00:13:24.571
And the second reason is that

00:13:24.571 --> 00:13:27.091
there is just so much to unpack,

00:13:27.161 --> 00:13:29.261
so we can’t do it justice in a

00:13:29.551 --> 00:13:31.351
small five minute section here.

00:13:32.271 --> 00:13:34.361
The good news is that we did just do

00:13:34.361 --> 00:13:37.391
an entire episode on the mad and tragic

00:13:37.401 --> 00:13:40.261
44 days of Liz Truss, so if you haven’t

00:13:40.261 --> 00:13:42.391
listened to that one already, then that

00:13:42.391 --> 00:13:45.021
one's for you, it’s episode number 327.

00:13:45.633 --> 00:13:48.463
Now, the final piece of unusual news

00:13:48.553 --> 00:13:50.403
is something that lots of people aren’t

00:13:50.433 --> 00:13:53.579
aware of outside the UK, and many people

00:13:53.679 --> 00:13:55.729
aren’t aware of even inside the UK.

00:13:56.559 --> 00:13:59.129
And this is related to the shifting

00:13:59.309 --> 00:14:01.769
demographics of the country, specifically,

00:14:01.769 --> 00:14:04.979
the increasing multiculturalism of the UK.

00:14:06.099 --> 00:14:08.749
This isn’t “news”, in so much as

00:14:08.879 --> 00:14:11.399
it's a gradual change, but there

00:14:11.579 --> 00:14:13.509
are some important pieces of news

00:14:13.509 --> 00:14:15.039
to mention that highlight the

00:14:15.419 --> 00:14:17.729
increasing diversity of the country.

00:14:18.789 --> 00:14:21.289
The first piece of “unusual news”

00:14:21.419 --> 00:14:23.119
is related to the publication of the

00:14:23.119 --> 00:14:26.479
results of the national Census, a big

00:14:26.489 --> 00:14:29.159
survey that is done of the UK population

00:14:29.379 --> 00:14:31.989
every 10 years, which tries to answer

00:14:32.149 --> 00:14:34.339
questions like “how many people live

00:14:34.339 --> 00:14:36.469
in the country?” and “who are they?”.

00:14:37.649 --> 00:14:39.679
The results started to be published

00:14:39.689 --> 00:14:42.559
this year, and had, for some,

00:14:42.829 --> 00:14:44.899
surprising results, especially

00:14:44.899 --> 00:14:46.959
with the fact that the UK has been

00:14:46.959 --> 00:14:49.059
painted by many outside the country

00:14:49.299 --> 00:14:51.889
as anti-foreigner and anti-immigrant.

00:14:52.879 --> 00:14:55.489
Of course, the Brexit vote gave people

00:14:55.489 --> 00:14:57.169
a pretty good reason to think that

00:14:57.169 --> 00:14:59.789
this was the case, but the results of

00:14:59.809 --> 00:15:01.829
the Census show that the country is

00:15:01.869 --> 00:15:03.779
different to what a lot of people think,

00:15:04.169 --> 00:15:06.849
and it is indeed much more multicultural

00:15:06.849 --> 00:15:09.189
than many large European countries.

00:15:09.969 --> 00:15:12.099
So, it might surprise you to find

00:15:12.099 --> 00:15:15.629
out that one in every six people in

00:15:15.639 --> 00:15:18.459
England and Wales was born outside

00:15:18.569 --> 00:15:22.589
the UK, a 33% increase from 2011.

00:15:23.609 --> 00:15:25.749
If you’re interested, the top five

00:15:25.749 --> 00:15:28.661
countries were, in this order, India,

00:15:28.971 --> 00:15:32.051
Poland, Pakistan, Romania and Ireland.

00:15:33.091 --> 00:15:36.411
This non-UK born population is highly

00:15:36.411 --> 00:15:38.341
concentrated in the cities, which

00:15:38.551 --> 00:15:40.881
tend to be more multicultural places.

00:15:41.841 --> 00:15:43.801
One area of London, for example,

00:15:44.131 --> 00:15:47.381
Brent, has 56% of its residents

00:15:47.521 --> 00:15:49.361
who were born outside the UK.

00:15:50.401 --> 00:15:52.901
Put simply, the UK is a lot more

00:15:52.901 --> 00:15:55.081
multicultural and multinational

00:15:55.141 --> 00:15:56.711
than many people think it is.

00:15:57.881 --> 00:16:00.585
And this is particularly important when

00:16:00.595 --> 00:16:02.928
one remembers that in the summer of 2022,

00:16:03.375 --> 00:16:05.685
the Prime Minister of the country was

00:16:05.715 --> 00:16:08.085
chosen only by members of the Conservative

00:16:08.085 --> 00:16:10.395
Party, fewer than a hundred thousand

00:16:10.435 --> 00:16:13.205
people voted for Liz Truss, and these

00:16:13.225 --> 00:16:16.645
voters were overwhelmingly, 97%, white,

00:16:16.995 --> 00:16:19.645
over half of them were over 60, and they

00:16:19.645 --> 00:16:21.865
lived primarily in the south of England.

00:16:22.815 --> 00:16:25.025
Essentially, the Prime Minister was

00:16:25.025 --> 00:16:27.245
voted in by a tiny proportion of the

00:16:27.245 --> 00:16:29.700
country’s population, and a proportion

00:16:29.720 --> 00:16:31.870
of the population that was utterly

00:16:32.010 --> 00:16:34.650
unrepresentative of the real electorate.

00:16:36.170 --> 00:16:38.390
Now, as you’ll remember, the Prime

00:16:38.390 --> 00:16:40.010
Minister that was chosen by the members

00:16:40.010 --> 00:16:42.260
of the Conservative Party, Liz Truss,

00:16:42.550 --> 00:16:44.240
didn’t do a very good job at all.

00:16:45.060 --> 00:16:47.420
Nevertheless, her tenure as Prime

00:16:47.420 --> 00:16:50.470
Minister did break some records, and not

00:16:50.520 --> 00:16:52.410
only for the shortest time in office.

00:16:53.300 --> 00:16:55.070
On September the 6th of this

00:16:55.090 --> 00:16:57.230
year, when Liz Truss announced

00:16:57.230 --> 00:16:59.480
her cabinet, a record was broken.

00:17:00.050 --> 00:17:01.890
It was the first time in British

00:17:01.890 --> 00:17:03.990
history that the “Great Offices of

00:17:03.990 --> 00:17:06.450
State” didn’t contain a white man.

00:17:07.250 --> 00:17:09.120
The “Great Offices of State” are the

00:17:09.120 --> 00:17:11.180
most important political jobs in the

00:17:11.180 --> 00:17:13.480
country: so that's the Prime Minister,

00:17:13.750 --> 00:17:15.829
the Chancellor of the Exchequer, which

00:17:15.829 --> 00:17:18.560
is basically the Minister of Finance, the

00:17:18.580 --> 00:17:20.740
Foreign Secretary and the Home Secretary.

00:17:21.830 --> 00:17:24.210
Now, these politicians might have been

00:17:24.480 --> 00:17:27.100
trailblazers in terms of who they were,

00:17:27.330 --> 00:17:29.460
but they were still useless politicians

00:17:29.540 --> 00:17:31.780
and they did huge damage to the country.

00:17:32.810 --> 00:17:34.870
As you may well know, after they were

00:17:34.880 --> 00:17:37.170
booted out, the country then broke a

00:17:37.170 --> 00:17:39.630
new record when it welcomed the first

00:17:39.790 --> 00:17:41.960
non-white Prime Minister in the form of

00:17:42.100 --> 00:17:44.850
Rishi Sunak, who has Indian heritage.

00:17:45.530 --> 00:17:48.045
And another fun-fact about Rishi Sunak

00:17:48.130 --> 00:17:50.700
is that, at 42 years old, he was the

00:17:50.700 --> 00:17:53.400
youngest Prime Minister in 200 years.

00:17:54.600 --> 00:17:56.780
Although Sunak might be representative

00:17:56.780 --> 00:17:58.900
of the changing demographics of

00:17:58.900 --> 00:18:00.920
the country, he has been criticised

00:18:01.132 --> 00:18:03.220
for being pretty unrepresentative

00:18:03.230 --> 00:18:05.180
in almost every other way.

00:18:06.493 --> 00:18:08.623
Specifically, his bank balance

00:18:08.653 --> 00:18:11.053
certainly is not representative of

00:18:11.053 --> 00:18:12.773
the average person in the country.

00:18:13.653 --> 00:18:15.693
When his wife’s fortune is taken

00:18:15.693 --> 00:18:18.213
into account, Sunak holds the record

00:18:18.373 --> 00:18:20.303
for being the richest ever British

00:18:20.323 --> 00:18:22.163
Prime Minister, with a combined

00:18:22.163 --> 00:18:24.883
fortune of almost a billion Euros.

00:18:26.303 --> 00:18:28.023
So, there you have it,

00:18:28.143 --> 00:18:30.712
the unusual news of 2022.

00:18:31.183 --> 00:18:33.783
This year the UK has broken records

00:18:33.783 --> 00:18:35.853
for the longest monarch, the world’s

00:18:35.853 --> 00:18:37.733
longest-serving female monarch, the

00:18:37.923 --> 00:18:39.843
richest Prime Minister, the youngest

00:18:39.853 --> 00:18:41.953
Prime Minister, the shortest-serving

00:18:41.953 --> 00:18:44.413
Prime Minister, it’s broken multicultural

00:18:44.413 --> 00:18:46.683
records, it has seen some extremely

00:18:46.693 --> 00:18:48.753
bad behaviour from politicians, and

00:18:48.913 --> 00:18:51.453
last but not least, some exceptional

00:18:51.463 --> 00:18:53.862
